headline: GM to bring Google's Gemini AI to cars, Meta cutting 600 jobs
summary: Yahoo Finance's John Hyland tracks Wednesday's top moving stocks and biggest market stories in this Market Minute. Meta (META) announced 600 job cuts in its artificial intelligence (AI) unit. General Motors (GM) unveiled plans to bring driver assist technology and Google's (GOOG, GOOGL) Gemini AI to its cars. Tesla (TSLA) is kicking off "Magnificent Seven" earnings after Wednesday's closing bell. Stay up to date on the latest market action, minute-by-minute, with Yahoo Finance's Market Minute.
